SummaryOfDirectChrtblActyGrp.Description1Txt: LUCY SPARROWTHE FOUNDATION ENTERED INTO AN AGREEMENT WITH ART PRODUCTION FUND (APL), A NEW YORK BASED PUBLIC CHARITY, TO SPONSOR AN ART EXHIBIT PROJECT ENTITLED LUCY SPARROW'S TAMPA DELI & CONVENIENCE STORE IN TAMPA, FL. THE EXHIBIT WAS FREE AND OPEN TO THE PUBLIC AND WAS ORIGINALLY SCHEDULED FOR EARLY 2021, WHEN THE CITY OF TAMPA WAS SCHEDULED TO HOST THE SUPER BOWL. THE ONSET OF THE CORONAVIRUS PANDEMIC RESULTED IN CANCELLING THE 2021 EXHIBIT AND RESCHEDULING FOR JANUARY 2022.
SummaryOfDirectChrtblActyGrp.Description2Txt: ARTWORK STORAGE-LOVE IS CALLINGTHE FOUNDATION OWNS YAYOI KUSAMA'S ART EXHIBIT ENTITLED "LOVE IS CALLING". DURING 2022 THERE WERE EXPENSES INCURRED FOR THE STORAGE AND INSURANCE FOR THE EXHIBIT IN A CLIMATE-CONTROLLED ART STORAGE WAREHOUSE. THIS ARTWORK WAS ON DISPLAY TO THE PUBLIC IN 2018 AT THE TAMPA MUSEUM OF ART AND WILL BE DISPLAYED FOR THE BENEFIT OF THE PUBLIC AGAIN IN THE FUTURE.

SumOfProgramRelatedInvstGrp.Description1Txt: TAMPA BAY INNOVATION HUB INC. THE FOUNDATION HAS PROVIDED TWO LOANS TO TAMPA BAY INNOVATION HUB, INC., DOING BUSINESS AS EMBARC COLLECTIVE TAMPA BAY. EMBARC COLLECTIVE IS A SECTION 501 (C)(3) PUBLIC CHARITY THAT HELPS TAMPA BAY'S STARTUP TALENT BUILD BOLD, SCALABLE, THRIVING COMPANIES VIA ITS EDUCATIONAL SUPPORT FOR ENTREPRENEURS. THE FIRST FOUNDATION LOAN PROVIDED NEEDED FUNDS TO COMPLETE THE REFURBISHMENT OF ITS LEASED FACILITY IN TAMPA, FL. THE SECOND LOAN PROVIDES A REVOLVING CREDIT FACILITY TO ASSIST EMBARC WITH CASH UNTIL IT CAN STABILIZE ITS OPERATIONS. BOTH LOANS ARE UNSECURED AND WERE PROVIDED AT THE APPLICABLE FEDERAL INTEREST RATE IN EFFECT AT THE TIME.
